	     <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform"><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=27649"><span id="Sage">Palarran</span></a><br /><b><span id="Sage">Sage</span></b><br /><span id="notbold">119 posts<br /><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Excellent [5.00]</td><td valign=top class="mform" width="100%"><p>Actually it's because 1 point of AC on an item does not add 1 point to the AC stat.<br/>I think someone found it to be 1.55 actual AC per 1 AC on an item, though it could be a formula that takes other things into account.&nbsp;&nbsp;1.55:1 would here though...3*1.55=4.65, which due to rounding could increase AC by 5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </p>&nbsp;<br /></td></tr>
